race.comment: AUTUNNO (11) was outclassed last start in open company at Eagle Farm - best to ignore that run. Made up a stack of ground to grab second the start before over 2000m on the Gold Coast poly. Big chance with a repeat of that effort. MAD ANA (9) won a 1900m Class 1 at Ballina two back then tackled a better race at Ipswich last time and was not disgraced. Very fit mare who poses a serious threat with just 54.5kgs after the claim. Matthew Dunn's BAILS (6) is a promising stayer who has only raced three times, winning the past two. Gave away a huge start before getting up here at this trip most recently. Hard to say she won't be winning again despite the class rise. INDY ROSE WARRIOR (1) has struggled of late but will find this a shade easier and the extra trip may be what she needs. TIETAR (2) won two on the trot over 1600m before a respectable effort last start in a Rosehill Highway. Steps up in journey now which won't do her chances any harm.
